Satat Jeevikoparjan Yojana (SJY).details:
&amp;quot;Satat Jeevikoparjan Yojana (SJY)&amp;quot;, launched by the Government of Bihar on August 5, 2018, aims to empower approximately 100,000 ultra-poor households by providing sustainable livelihood opportunities. The program, implemented by the Bihar Rural Livelihoods Promotion Society (JEEViKA), employs the globally recognized Graduation Approach. This initiative supports targeted households with asset transfers, capacity-building training, livelihood gap assistance, and mentoring for 24 months, ensuring long-term self-reliance. Beneficiaries also gain access to insurance, public entitlements, and relief support during crises like COVID-19.
